  "_comment": "Three-way contract for the due-reminder calculation: prospect.reminders.due_reminders (Python spec) vs n8n/code/compute-due-reminders.js (live JS port, Notion-shaped input) vs recorded expectation. `python: match` cases must agree three ways; `python: invalid` cases pin a KNOWN DIVERGENCE — the strict Python validator raises InvalidDeadline while the lenient live JS port silently proceeds (reported in docs/PLAN-consolidation.md, phase-4 deferred list). `frozen_now_utc` is the instant injected into the JS sandbox; `as_of` is that instant's calendar date in the node's hardcoded America/Mexico_City timezone (UTC-6, no DST) and the date handed to Python.",
